<br>
</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ubethude.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bethude</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Wizard</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>5/10/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>11:27:20 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Tormax</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I'm *guessing* that stacking for flowing thoughts works as follows:<br>
<br>
If you have an item with the same Flowing Thoughts effect (say flowing thoughts I), it will not stack with another item with the same effect.  However, it would stack with a flowing thoughts II, III, etc.  <br>
<br>
They handle melee haste item stacking by just giving each item the same effect name (&quot;haste&quot;).  It's probably veran't intention that the flowing thought items don't stack, but they probably do if you mix the different levels of the effect.  I don't think the game engine allows for any stacking restrictions on items except based on effect name.  <br>
</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#33333><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uragbert.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ragbert</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.lpg.fi/~jsalo/smr10.gif BORDER=0></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Apprentice</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>5/10/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>12:03:34 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.lpg.fi/~jsalo/ragicon.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Tormax</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I did comment to Absor on the Flowing Thought post. His point about caster haste being different to melee haste is different thing because caster mana is spent on other things than just damage does not really apply to all caster classes. What else does a wizard spend mana on really that risks exploits and unbalance? Quicker teleporting?<br>
<br>
Complete Heal and maybe entire healing itself is definitely an area that might introduce yet more unbalance to the game, but it is hard to see the case with wizards whose spell line is so greatly limited. I recommend other people to send him a note to please do not generalize &quot;casters&quot; in this context.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usolkan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Solkan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC= http://solkaneq.homestead.com/files/button.gif BORDER=0></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Wizard</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>5/10/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>5:16:12 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Tormax</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Check it out...<br>
